The statement '(void) upload_data_size;' is an executed no‑op used only to silence an unused‑parameter warning. Its removal would not change program behaviour (other than compiler diagnostics), so it is an operation executed but with no effect and therefore qualifies as dead code under MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
